Vice President Kamala Harris spoke at the Treasury Department about the importance of supporting working families in America. She acknowledged the challenges faced by women in the workforce during the pandemic, including layoffs, business closures, and lack of childcare. Harris emphasized the need to get women back to work and highlighted the economic benefits of their full participation. The Treasury Department released a report titled "The Economics of Childcare," which emphasized the high costs and limited accessibility of childcare in the United States. Harris called for a significant public investment in the childcare industry and expressed the Biden administration's commitment to supporting and strengthening working families through the Build Back Better agenda. The agenda aims to extend the Child Tax Credit, expand paid family leave, lower childcare costs, and make universal preschool a reality. Harris shared her personal experience of relying on childcare support and emphasized the importance of providing similar support to all working parents. She concluded by introducing Treasury Secretary Janet Yellen.